{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"code":["🧬 Theme version: 2.3.0"],"syntax":null,"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This is the Sosh theme any Sosh product must use, and cannot be subclassed.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It embeds also in its target the Sosh brand colors which are not shared nor exposed in lower level targets or outside any module not depending to it.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"In other words, this "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesSosh\/documentation\/OUDSThemesSosh\/SoshTheme"},{"type":"text","text":" is based on the abstract "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSTheme"},{"type":"text","text":", uses all the "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Orange Unified Design System"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" kit and brings the Sosh brand colors and assets.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"tip","name":"Tip","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This theme embeds and registers the fonts for the Sosh theme, you just need to use the theme object as is."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside"},{"style":"important","type":"aside","name":"Important","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Sosh theme does not embed colors for charts yet and is read only: it cannot be subclassed or derivated"}]}]},{"text":"How to use the theme","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"How-to-use-the-theme"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can use "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesSosh\/documentation\/OUDSThemesSosh\/SoshTheme"},{"type":"text","text":" directly. To use the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesSosh\/documentation\/OUDSThemesSosh\/SoshTheme"},{"type":"text","text":" without further modifications, you will have to use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSThemeableView"},{"type":"text","text":" for your root view and give it an instance of "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesSosh\/documentation\/OUDSThemesSosh\/SoshTheme"},{"type":"text","text":". Keep in mind the themes are "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Swift class objects"}]},{"type":"text","text":" and can be heavy, so you may use only as instance as singleton and not store any properties."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["@main","struct YourApp: App {","    var body: some Scene {","        WindowGroup {","            OUDSThemeableView(theme: SoshTheme()) {","                \/\/ Your root view","            }","        }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Then, in your views, you can simply use the theme through an environment variable to get the tokens:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["struct SomeView: View {","","    \/\/ Get OUDS environment variable for theme thanks to themeable view","    @Environment(\\.theme) var theme","    ","    var body: some View {","        ","        \/\/ Use the theme to retrieve the tokens","        \/\/ For spaces: theme.spaces","        \/\/ For sizes: theme.sizes","        \/\/ For borders: theme.borders","        \/\/ For elevations: theme.elevations","        \/\/ For opacities: theme.opacities","        \/\/ For colors: theme.colors","        \/\/ For button configuration: theme.button","        \/\/ For link configuration: theme.link","        \/\/ Etc.","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","text":"How to tune the theme","level":2,"anchor":"How-to-tune-the-theme"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You cannot tune the Sosh theme.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Typography","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Typography"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Sosh theme uses its Sosh font and must not use others."}],"ty